Phase 2: Coverage Metrics Computation - Tests + Implementation

Tests written (Red phase):
- 9 new tests in test_reporter.py for compute_file_summary() and compute_summary()
- Test full coverage (100% line, 100% branch)
- Test partial coverage (3/5 lines = 60%, 1/2 branches = 50%)
- Test zero coverage (0% all)
- Test uncovered_lines list identification
- Test if_true/if_false branch pair
- Test elif_true, loop_body, match_case branch types
- Test multi-file aggregation
- Test zero-coverage files included in summary
- Test missing file in coverage data treated as 0 hits

Implementation (Green phase):
- compute_file_summary(file_plan, file_data) -> FileSummary
  - Counts all lines as total_lines (both statement and branch)
  - Counts branch-type lines as total_branches
  - hit_count > 0 means covered
  - uncovered_lines = line numbers with 0 hits
  - Handles division by zero (empty file)
- compute_summary(plan, data) -> CoverageSummary
  - Builds file_id -> FileCoverage lookup
  - Missing files get empty FileCoverage (0 hits)
  - Aggregates covered/total counts across all files

